<div align='center'><font size='4'><b>STUDIO T CREATES BUZZ IN MILLSBERRY</b></font><br>
<img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20071115.jpg' border='1'>
</div>
<div id='gazette_byline''><em>By Audrey Smythe-Wei<br>Editor-in-chief</em></div>
<b>Thursday, November 15, 2007</b> &mdash; The grand opening of <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/studio.phtml">Studio T</a>,  the new T-shirt design lab constructed by Loretta Rivers, took place this week. Thousands of Millsberry citizens and fashion enthusiasts gathered for the ribbon cutting ceremony that took place.<br><br><a href="http://www.millsberry.com/studio.phtml">Studio T</a> is a fully functional T-shirt design lab, where anyone can come in and design their own completely customized T-shirt in a matter of minutes. With all of the different design options, there are literally endless possibilities. New T-shirt designs and styles have been spotted all over Millsberry since the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/studio.phtml">Studio T</a> opening.<br><br>&quot;This is a truly groundbreaking addition to the city. Never before have I seen anything like this. Loretta has really outdone herself. It will be very exciting to see all of the new designs that the citizens of Millsberry produce. I may even consider turning Friday into Casual T-shirt Friday at my Office. I&#039;ve got a lot of ideas, and I really want to be able to show everyone at work my new customized T-shirts&quot;, said Mayor Trumble at the grand opening ceremony.<br><br><a href="http://www.millsberry.com/studio.phtml">Studio T</a> has proved to be a lot of hard work for Loretta Rivers, the creator of the T-shirt lab. <br>
<br>
&quot;In the beginning, I just wanted to produce something really special for the people of Millsberry, something that they could make their own and that would be one-of-a-kind. Then I thought to myself, &quot;What better way to do that than by being able to design your own T-shirts?&quot; It just made sense&quot;, commented Rivers.<br><br>The <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/studio.phtml">Studio T</a> design lab took nearly half a year to construct. Its construction was paired with the redesign of the Millsberry clothing store that has since been renamed &quot;Wearhouse: Clothing by L. Rivers&quot;. <br><br>&quot;You really need to love what you&#039;re wearing, and who knows what you love better than you?&quot; asked Rivers at the opening.<br><br>It seems as though L. Rivers has found a way to give people exactly what they want, by letting them do that for her.<br></div>


<br><hr><br>

<div id='gazette_story'>
<div align='center'><font size='3'><b>MUST HAVE ITEMS FOR THANKSGIVING</b></font><br>
</div>
<br>
Thanksgiving is only a week away, and it&#039;s time to start thinking about how you&#039;re going to set your table to present your cornucopia of Turkey Day delight  (a.k.a. dinner). <br><br>With all of the Thanksgiving food, you&#039;re going to need some extra dining accoutrements. Luckily, just for this special occasion, there will be brand new Thanksgiving items available next week.<br><br>These items are sure to be a smash hit at any Thanksgiving gathering, so keep a look out in the <a href=http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=3>Millsberry Furniture Store</a> next week to get your hands on some.<br><br>In other news, the <i>Millsberry <i>Gazette</i></i> would like to congratulate the three winners of this year&#039;s Halloween Trick or Treating event. <br><br>The winners who were rewarded trophies for the event were: in third place <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/home/?user=samary1995">samary1995</a>, in second place <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/home/?user=lil_shorty0706">lil_shorty0706</a>, and in first place <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/home/?user=imagin64">imagin64</a>. <br><br>We thank you all for participating, and we hope you enjoyed your Halloween.<br></div>
